WEBVTT

00:08.809 --> 00:10.744
[***]

00:58.159 --> 01:00.728
[OPERA MUSIC PLAYING]

01:05.199 --> 01:08.136
NORTON [OVER INTERCOM]:
Ladies and gentlemen,
you are now looking

01:08.169 --> 01:14.308
at the iridescent glow
that is the Hermagon Ultra.

01:14.342 --> 01:17.745
The dance of interstellar dust
within the supernova

01:17.778 --> 01:20.381
is what makes this sight
so rare

01:20.414 --> 01:23.884
and so popular among visitors
to the Hermagon Aurora.

01:23.917 --> 01:28.122
Luckily for you folks
on Dream Weaver 9

01:28.156 --> 01:31.192
the conditions today
are perfectly clear.

01:31.225 --> 01:34.828
Ideal for a sighting
of this unique chemical miracle.

01:37.765 --> 01:39.733
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

01:52.680 --> 01:56.217
COMPUTER:
Color selected.

01:56.250 --> 01:57.385
[ALL GASPING]

02:01.955 --> 02:04.425
NORTON:
At its finest,
ladies and gentlemen,

02:04.458 --> 02:06.894
the Hermagon Aurora
is enough to make you

02:06.927 --> 02:10.731
believe in God all over again.

02:17.271 --> 02:19.740
[***]

02:26.380 --> 02:28.516
NORTON:
Astral Dreams has been proud
to bring you

02:28.549 --> 02:30.684
the excursion to the
Centaura B Star System today--

02:30.718 --> 02:32.686
Dream Weaver 9 is now...

02:32.720 --> 02:37.625
SYNTH ATTENDANT:
...Dream Weaver survey
in the Primotel foyer

02:37.658 --> 02:40.228
so that we can make
your next journey with us

02:40.261 --> 02:42.696
even more fulfilling.

02:42.730 --> 02:47.468
[SYNTH WOMAN MOANING]

03:06.254 --> 03:08.622
ANDREWS:
Rats in a sewer, my friends.

03:08.656 --> 03:10.391
You're rats in a sewer.

03:13.461 --> 03:15.529
Hi.
All right.

03:18.632 --> 03:20.734
Here we go, then.

03:20.768 --> 03:22.736
There's a health and safety,

03:22.770 --> 03:25.606
engine report,
customer satisfaction survey.

03:25.639 --> 03:26.974
Happy campers?

03:27.007 --> 03:29.243
There was a complaint
about the sound quality

03:29.277 --> 03:31.512
on Deck 3, again.

03:31.545 --> 03:33.447
Are you ever
gonna fix that speaker?

03:33.481 --> 03:35.349
Oh, uh...

03:38.752 --> 03:41.455
A lot of dust out there today.
Oh, yeah.

03:41.489 --> 03:43.291
Yeah, I used the vis-augment.

03:43.324 --> 03:44.892
I don't think anybody
noticed it though.

03:46.360 --> 03:48.862
Look at
the sorry state of man.

03:48.896 --> 03:51.865
[SYNTH WOMAN CONTINUES MOANING]

03:51.899 --> 03:53.434
What the fuck is that?

03:56.504 --> 03:58.372
It's my happy time.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.709
All right, then, Tonto.

04:01.742 --> 04:03.811
Let's do this
and then we can head home.

04:03.844 --> 04:06.414
[***]

04:06.447 --> 04:08.849
[MECHANISMS WHIRRING]

04:14.322 --> 04:17.958
So next week we have
two package tours

04:17.991 --> 04:20.060
to the Ice Flows on Prigma 27.

04:20.093 --> 04:21.495
I'll do those.

04:21.529 --> 04:23.030
Bit keen, aren't we?

04:23.063 --> 04:25.032
I like the Ice Flows.
They're pretty.

04:25.065 --> 04:27.034
And we got
a pre-booked wedding party

04:27.067 --> 04:29.703
heading to the Sybil Nebula.
Do they need a band?

04:29.737 --> 04:32.840
Already booked it
from Primus 3.

04:32.873 --> 04:35.008
I had the honor
of listening to the demo.

04:35.042 --> 04:39.547
The musical taste of these
people defies fucking belief.

04:39.580 --> 04:40.848
Put it on there.

04:40.881 --> 04:42.950
I'd rather pour
hot oil down me ears.

04:45.453 --> 04:48.789
You fancy a beer or three?
End of the week?

04:48.822 --> 04:51.091
I got to get home.

04:51.124 --> 04:52.593
Barbara's waiting for me.

04:52.626 --> 04:53.861
Oh, is she now?

04:53.894 --> 04:55.095
[SMACKS LIPS]

04:55.128 --> 04:57.598
I'd invite you back,
but, you know.

04:57.631 --> 04:58.966
I know.

04:58.999 --> 05:01.702
Barbara's getting ready
for Primo Central.

05:01.735 --> 05:02.970
Your transfer confirmed?

05:03.003 --> 05:04.372
Not yet.

05:04.405 --> 05:05.706
Linus Primo does love

05:05.739 --> 05:07.341
to keep a man hanging on.

05:07.375 --> 05:09.343
I am going to get it.

05:09.377 --> 05:10.978
It's just a question
of process.

05:11.011 --> 05:12.680
It better be.
That girl is dreaming

05:12.713 --> 05:14.348
of the high life,
my friend.

05:14.382 --> 05:16.384
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

05:16.417 --> 05:20.053
On the door there is a sign
saying, "Closed".

05:20.087 --> 05:23.491
I wonder what it means.

05:23.524 --> 05:25.526
Do you wanna get the Loop
back to the condos?

05:25.559 --> 05:28.629
Uh, I think I'll see this
to the end.

05:28.662 --> 05:30.431
Just reached
an interesting plot point.

05:32.700 --> 05:34.835
ANDREWS:
Can you read, asshole?
We're closed.

05:34.868 --> 05:37.605
There's an IMT console
in the Primotel

05:37.638 --> 05:39.573
for any online reservations.

05:39.607 --> 05:41.008
There's also
a customer care number

05:41.041 --> 05:42.776
right in front
of your fucking eyes.

05:42.810 --> 05:43.944
Hmph.

05:45.546 --> 05:46.680
I'll get it, I'll get it.

05:51.485 --> 05:52.853
Hello there.

05:54.755 --> 05:56.156
Oh, my.

05:56.189 --> 05:58.592
[***]

06:00.761 --> 06:02.496
I'm sorry, uh...

06:03.964 --> 06:05.499
We're not open.

06:05.533 --> 06:07.034
You'll have to come back
next week.

06:07.067 --> 06:09.470
RB29:
Miss Gordon has lost
her hearing.

06:09.503 --> 06:10.804
Excuse me?

06:10.838 --> 06:13.774
Miss Gordon is deaf.

06:13.807 --> 06:15.075
Uh, I see.

06:15.108 --> 06:17.077
My name is Irma Gordon.

06:17.110 --> 06:19.413
And I want you to take me
on a tour.

06:19.447 --> 06:21.782
I understand, madam,
but we're now closed.

06:23.584 --> 06:25.453
Can you tell her that
there are no tours

06:25.486 --> 06:27.020
until next week?

06:27.054 --> 06:28.822
I can give her
a physical handout

06:28.856 --> 06:30.691
of our available destinations.

06:30.724 --> 06:32.192
If she likes.

06:32.225 --> 06:34.995
But if she's not proficient
on the network system

06:35.028 --> 06:36.864
she'll have to come back
on Monday.

06:36.897 --> 06:40.000
I want you to take me
on a tour to Earth.

06:40.033 --> 06:41.635
Did you--?
Didn't you hear the man?

06:41.669 --> 06:43.170
We're closed, sweetheart.
All right?

06:43.203 --> 06:45.506
She's deaf.
Closed. Shut.

06:45.539 --> 06:47.541
No happy holiday today.

06:47.575 --> 06:50.444
She said she wants
to go to Earth.

06:50.478 --> 06:52.546
Well, she's not deaf,
she's crazy.

06:52.580 --> 06:54.648
RB29:
Miss Gordon has traveled
a long way

06:54.682 --> 06:56.450
from her home on Riga 2.

06:56.484 --> 06:59.019
[MECHANISMS WHIR]

06:59.052 --> 07:02.523
She wishes to charter a ship
to take her to Earth.

07:02.556 --> 07:04.091
ANDREWS:
Listen, my cranky little pal,

07:04.124 --> 07:06.159
we can't take
Miss Gordon to Earth

07:06.193 --> 07:08.161
because Earth no longer exists.

07:08.195 --> 07:11.131
We don't take passengers
to nonexistent destinations.

07:11.164 --> 07:12.700
Strict company policy.

07:12.733 --> 07:16.169
RB29:
Miss Gordon is 342 years old.

07:16.203 --> 07:19.673
She flew the craft personally
to get here from Riga 2.

07:19.707 --> 07:21.542
ANDREWS:
Then she can stay
in the Primotel

07:21.575 --> 07:22.843
and fly back home tomorrow.

07:22.876 --> 07:24.578
I'll tell you what. Lady?

07:24.612 --> 07:27.581
Because it's the end of the week
and I like your face,

07:27.615 --> 07:30.918
I'm gonna give you an
Astral Dreams promotional coupon

07:30.951 --> 07:33.120
entitling you
to a free cocktail

07:33.153 --> 07:35.255
on the house when you book
your Primotel room.

07:35.288 --> 07:38.826
Any cocktail of your choice,
except the Primobellini

07:38.859 --> 07:40.227
where there is
a two bit surcharge.

07:40.260 --> 07:42.095
You can't say fairer than that.

07:42.129 --> 07:44.798
She has two kilo positive
to pay you.

07:44.832 --> 07:47.100
[***]

07:47.134 --> 07:48.936
Excuse me?

07:48.969 --> 07:51.138
RB29:
She is willing to pay
Astral Dreams

07:51.171 --> 07:53.541
two kilo positive to take her.

07:53.574 --> 07:56.176
If you're wondering about
method of transaction,

07:56.209 --> 07:58.946
Miss Gordon does not have
a cyber account.

07:58.979 --> 08:02.683
So she would have
to pay you in cash.

08:07.921 --> 08:10.057
[***]

08:10.090 --> 08:12.893
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

08:12.926 --> 08:14.862
ANDREWS:
This is Andrews at Primo 241.

08:14.895 --> 08:16.897
I need an urgent
data-feed on Earth,

08:16.930 --> 08:21.602
a planet in the solar system
2483B65, now extinct.

08:21.635 --> 08:25.939
Also need a match-up on current
Astral Dreams tour destinations.

08:25.973 --> 08:28.542
Closest approximation
to size, color,

08:28.576 --> 08:30.578
tech and chem specifications.

08:30.611 --> 08:32.813
COMPUTER:
We have six matches
to your request.

08:32.846 --> 08:35.048
Okay, give them to me.

08:35.082 --> 08:36.917
Too far.

08:36.950 --> 08:38.719
Way too far.

08:38.752 --> 08:40.087
Too big.

08:40.120 --> 08:41.822
Do you wanna tell me
what you're doing?

08:41.855 --> 08:44.992
Jesus, that's pink.
Earth was not pink.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.960
Okay, this is more like it.

08:46.994 --> 08:51.131
"Emphor 3. Three days
hyper-flight. One moon.

08:51.164 --> 08:54.935
"Third planet in nine
in a solar system dominated

08:54.968 --> 08:57.971
by one major sun. Blue color."

08:58.005 --> 09:00.641
Perfect match, my friend.

09:01.942 --> 09:03.844
That's not blue, it's gray.

09:05.646 --> 09:07.080
It's blue-y gray.

09:07.114 --> 09:09.683
It's a dead rock.
Doesn't even have any oxygen.

09:09.717 --> 09:11.819
She doesn't want to breathe it,
she wants to see it.

09:11.852 --> 09:13.654
I'm not doing it.
Look.

09:13.687 --> 09:15.989
She wants Earth,
we give her Earth.

09:16.023 --> 09:17.290
It takes us a week.

09:17.324 --> 09:18.792
We cancel all tours,

09:18.826 --> 09:20.894
we submit a TC32
to maintenance central

09:20.928 --> 09:23.096
tell them the Dream Weaver 9
is damaged.

09:23.130 --> 09:25.666
It isn't damaged.
Then I'll damage it.

09:25.699 --> 09:27.768
I'll jerry the engine
on our return.

09:27.801 --> 09:30.838
The crone's happy, she goes back
to her weird little outpost

09:30.871 --> 09:33.707
in God-knows-fucking-where,
we keep her visit off the books.

09:33.741 --> 09:35.108
No paperwork, nothing.

09:35.142 --> 09:39.112
And you and I
are one kilo positive richer.

09:39.146 --> 09:41.649
It's five years' salary, Brian.

09:41.682 --> 09:43.684
Imagine what we could do
with that.

09:45.786 --> 09:47.120
You do what you want,

09:47.154 --> 09:49.189
but I'm not gonna blow my chance
at Primo Central

09:49.222 --> 09:50.824
doing this crazy shit.

09:50.858 --> 09:52.059
You have to.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.762
It's a two-man craft, minimum.

09:54.795 --> 09:57.197
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

09:59.199 --> 10:00.801
It's Barbara.

10:03.270 --> 10:04.872
Ugh...

10:05.973 --> 10:07.207
Leave it to me, I can--

10:07.240 --> 10:09.609
Don't say a fucking word.

10:13.814 --> 10:15.182
Hey, babe.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.850
Where are you?

10:16.884 --> 10:19.720
I'm still at work.
Something came up. I'm sorry.

10:19.753 --> 10:21.254
That's okay.

10:21.288 --> 10:22.790
Are you on your own?

10:22.823 --> 10:24.324
Yeah. Yep. I am.

10:24.357 --> 10:26.860
I'm just about
to walk out the door.

10:26.894 --> 10:28.328
Have you heard anything?

10:28.361 --> 10:30.230
About?
What do you think?

10:30.263 --> 10:31.932
About the transfer.

10:31.965 --> 10:34.001
Can we talk about this
when I get home?

10:34.034 --> 10:36.036
I think you should
check your vid mail, Brian.

10:37.270 --> 10:38.739
Okay.

10:42.743 --> 10:44.177
Hey there.

10:44.211 --> 10:47.047
This is Linus Primo.

10:47.080 --> 10:49.216
I wanted to take
the opportunity

10:49.249 --> 10:51.919
to message you personally

10:51.952 --> 10:54.988
to say that,
unfortunately, this time

10:55.022 --> 10:58.258
you did not succeed
in your application

10:58.291 --> 11:01.895
to transfer to Head Office
here at Primo Central.

11:01.929 --> 11:04.832
I know this must come
as a disappointment to you

11:04.865 --> 11:06.834
as this is your--
BARBARA: Fifth.

11:06.867 --> 11:08.001
--Application.

11:11.371 --> 11:13.273
You see,
I was under the impression

11:13.306 --> 11:14.875
we'd be here for two years.

11:14.908 --> 11:16.343
It's been four years.

11:16.376 --> 11:18.946
And something tells me
it's going to be six.

11:18.979 --> 11:21.414
And still I do my hair
three times a day

11:21.448 --> 11:23.884
and still I go
to the Primotel bar

11:23.917 --> 11:25.085
and I sit alone.

11:25.118 --> 11:26.319
I'm gonna deal with it.

11:26.353 --> 11:28.021
You don't get it, do you?

11:28.055 --> 11:30.190
You don't mean
anything to them.

11:30.223 --> 11:32.926
So how can you
possibly deal with it?

11:38.298 --> 11:41.434
[***]

11:52.245 --> 11:55.382
[***]

12:03.023 --> 12:06.760
ANDREWS [OVER INTERCOM]:
Okay, folks, we're just passing
Omega 5

12:06.794 --> 12:08.428
well known
for its high luminosity,

12:08.461 --> 12:11.398
which you would normally see
out of your window.

12:11.431 --> 12:14.101
Sadly we've a lot
of dust cloud today

12:14.134 --> 12:16.770
and I'm not sure you'll be lucky
in that regard.

12:16.804 --> 12:20.273
And then we'll be traveling past
Alpha Centauri

12:20.307 --> 12:24.845
until we reach
solar system 2483B65.

12:24.878 --> 12:27.280
Home of Planet Earth.

12:43.363 --> 12:45.165
Your Castor Fireball,
Miss Gordon.

12:45.198 --> 12:47.500
Thank you.
Double the vodka as requested.

12:51.271 --> 12:52.539
Can I get you anything, sir?
Mm.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.880
My grandmother

12:59.913 --> 13:03.350
was 279 years old
when she died.

13:03.383 --> 13:06.086
A spring chicken
compared to me,

13:06.119 --> 13:08.788
but at the time
it was an achievement.

13:12.192 --> 13:13.961
I remember her

13:13.994 --> 13:18.565
sitting on our porch on Riga 2.

13:18.598 --> 13:21.068
She had me on her knee

13:21.101 --> 13:23.871
and she told me
about her life on Earth

13:23.904 --> 13:25.973
as a child.

13:26.006 --> 13:29.542
Her father had a cabin
in the forest.

13:29.576 --> 13:33.380
A place called Carolina.

13:33.413 --> 13:37.250
The cabin was made of a wood
called oak, I believe.

13:37.284 --> 13:39.119
He was a logger.

13:39.152 --> 13:41.488
He was a real woodsman.
Had some opinions

13:41.521 --> 13:43.423
that wouldn't go down
very well today.

13:43.456 --> 13:45.058
[LAUGHS]

13:48.261 --> 13:50.597
IRMA [ON SCREEN]:
My grandmother's name
was Laura Cade.

13:50.630 --> 13:52.265
She married my grandfather,

13:52.299 --> 13:56.003
Bill Gordon. Hence my name,
Irma Louise Gordon,

13:56.036 --> 13:59.239
She told me
that there was a place

13:59.272 --> 14:02.542
about five miles
from the cabin,

14:02.575 --> 14:05.913
called Elk River Falls.

14:05.946 --> 14:09.049
It was a beautiful
waterfall cascading

14:09.082 --> 14:11.018
into a natural pool of water

14:11.051 --> 14:13.286
so clear you could see
the bottom.

14:13.320 --> 14:15.322
Ha. Well,
I don't really know

14:15.355 --> 14:18.391
if I should
tell you this, but...

14:18.425 --> 14:20.293
on summer days

14:20.327 --> 14:24.097
she and Bill
would head over to the Falls

14:24.131 --> 14:27.867
and they would swim naked.

14:29.937 --> 14:31.104
Not a stitch on them.

14:32.672 --> 14:34.141
She told me

14:34.174 --> 14:38.245
that was the best feeling
she'd ever had.

14:38.278 --> 14:40.313
And I always
remember thinking

14:40.347 --> 14:43.550
"I would love
to see that place.

14:43.583 --> 14:46.519
To swim
in that clear water."

14:46.553 --> 14:49.656
Elk River Falls.

14:49.689 --> 14:51.925
Carolina.

14:53.426 --> 14:55.528
That's where
I want you to take me.

15:01.668 --> 15:03.370
You should tell her
that we can't

15:03.403 --> 15:05.973
necessarily locate
specific destinations.

15:06.006 --> 15:07.574
IRMA:
Of course,
you're going to tell me

15:07.607 --> 15:09.142
that things have changed.

15:09.176 --> 15:11.378
That Earth back then
is not Earth today,

15:11.411 --> 15:13.046
or some such thing, but...

15:13.080 --> 15:14.581
[SIGHS]

15:14.614 --> 15:18.018
If my life has taught me
anything, Mr. Norton

15:18.051 --> 15:20.387
it is that some places
want to change.

15:20.420 --> 15:22.489
And some places
don't want to change.

15:22.522 --> 15:27.660
And I think I know
which one Elk River is.

15:27.694 --> 15:30.530
[***]

15:30.563 --> 15:32.432
Do you?

15:55.522 --> 15:57.724
Does the Dream Weaver
always fly

15:57.757 --> 15:59.659
with such a small crew?

16:01.294 --> 16:03.163
Well, there'd
normally be four,

16:03.196 --> 16:05.065
including hospitality
and security.

16:05.098 --> 16:06.533
But because
of the late booking,

16:06.566 --> 16:08.501
we couldn't reach
the right people.

16:08.535 --> 16:11.004
[WHIRS]

16:11.038 --> 16:13.106
And Mr. Andrews?

16:13.140 --> 16:17.210
Does he normally fly
with the crafts?

16:17.244 --> 16:19.679
Sometimes.

16:19.712 --> 16:22.515
When there are VIP's
like yourselves on board.

16:22.549 --> 16:25.685
Why was there no paperwork
completed before we left?

16:25.718 --> 16:28.355
Well, we'll do that
when we get back.

16:28.388 --> 16:30.723
We didn't wanna burden her
with any formalities.

16:30.757 --> 16:32.225
[WHIRS]

16:32.259 --> 16:34.127
You took her money.
Yes.

16:34.161 --> 16:35.595
As a deposit.

16:35.628 --> 16:38.698
Mr. Andrews
took all of her money.

16:40.367 --> 16:42.469
Look, we're here, aren't we?

16:43.836 --> 16:46.273
This is what she wanted.

16:46.306 --> 16:47.807
[WHIRS]

16:47.840 --> 16:50.643
Miss Gordon is old.

16:50.677 --> 16:52.345
She trusts people.

16:54.714 --> 16:57.184
She is very old.
Yeah, she is.

16:57.217 --> 17:00.453
Miss Gordon has
a heart condition.

17:00.487 --> 17:03.090
She will die
in the next two months.

17:12.099 --> 17:14.067
I'm very sorry
to hear that.

17:14.101 --> 17:17.070
This will be
her very last trip.

17:17.104 --> 17:19.139
[***]

17:19.172 --> 17:20.707
Excuse me.

17:29.582 --> 17:31.518
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

17:36.389 --> 17:38.091
[KNOCKS LOUDLY]

17:53.573 --> 17:56.443
Sorry.
I knocked on the door.

17:56.476 --> 17:58.645
I don't think
you heard me. Um...

18:00.180 --> 18:01.781
Your complimentary
hot beverage, ma'am.

18:01.814 --> 18:05.252
Thank you, young man.
Just leave it on the table.

18:09.622 --> 18:11.158
Goodnight.
Stay a while.

18:11.191 --> 18:12.759
I should really be going.

18:12.792 --> 18:14.861
I'm sure Mr. Andrews
is more than capable

18:14.894 --> 18:17.830
of flying this craft
by himself.

18:17.864 --> 18:19.466
I suppose he is.

18:22.602 --> 18:23.770
I don't often use this.

18:26.773 --> 18:29.276
As it can be more
of a barrier than an aid,

18:29.309 --> 18:31.110
but just for today.

18:38.851 --> 18:40.620
Now, just speak normally.

18:40.653 --> 18:41.788
Don't mumble.

18:43.590 --> 18:44.757
Tell me about yourself.

18:44.791 --> 18:46.659
[SCOFFS]

18:46.693 --> 18:48.861
Oh, there's not
much to tell.

18:48.895 --> 18:50.797
[***]

18:53.500 --> 18:55.702
I was born on Primo 76.

18:55.735 --> 18:58.338
It's
a nice place.

18:58.371 --> 19:01.941
My father was an administrator
for Primobility

19:01.974 --> 19:03.676
the parent transport
company.

19:05.578 --> 19:06.846
When I graduated,

19:06.879 --> 19:10.350
I just fell
into leisure and tourism.

19:10.383 --> 19:11.551
Do you like it?

19:11.584 --> 19:13.486
Yeah.

19:13.520 --> 19:15.154
It's a good career path.

19:16.623 --> 19:18.925
We'd like to eventually
end up at Primo Central.

19:18.958 --> 19:20.793
So...

19:20.827 --> 19:22.629
We?

19:22.662 --> 19:23.863
I have a girlfriend.

19:23.896 --> 19:25.265
Barbara.

19:25.298 --> 19:27.434
Mm, I bet she's pretty.

19:27.467 --> 19:28.701
She is.

19:28.735 --> 19:30.703
We've been together
five years.

19:30.737 --> 19:32.339
And why haven't you
married her?

19:32.372 --> 19:34.574
I plan to.

19:34.607 --> 19:36.243
When the time is right.

19:41.881 --> 19:43.383
Do you love her?

19:43.416 --> 19:45.218
Who, Barbara?

19:45.252 --> 19:46.753
Of course.

19:51.658 --> 19:52.792
What's wrong?

19:55.027 --> 19:56.963
I don't know.

19:56.996 --> 19:59.532
It kind of feels
like I'm on the record.

19:59.566 --> 20:02.769
[LAUGHS]
Like I've ended up
in court somehow.

20:02.802 --> 20:04.471
[IRMA CHUCKLES]

20:04.504 --> 20:07.407
Are you afraid to testify
to your love, Mr. Norton?

20:07.440 --> 20:08.608
No, not at all.

20:08.641 --> 20:10.610
That would suggest
you are not certain

20:10.643 --> 20:11.778
in your choice.

20:13.580 --> 20:15.348
I love Barbara.

20:18.318 --> 20:20.287
We just...

20:23.923 --> 20:25.625
[SOFTLY]
We just what?

20:27.527 --> 20:30.530
Don't always
want the same thing.

20:30.563 --> 20:31.931
That's all.

20:34.801 --> 20:36.936
She wants Primo Central,
doesn't she?

20:38.004 --> 20:39.372
Yeah.

20:41.641 --> 20:42.942
And you?

20:44.977 --> 20:46.846
What do you want,
Mr. Norton?

20:48.781 --> 20:50.983
[***]

20:54.887 --> 20:56.556
I should go.

20:59.626 --> 21:01.461
Good night, young man.

21:09.936 --> 21:11.604
[SIGHS]

21:11.638 --> 21:14.541
[***]

21:17.444 --> 21:20.613
[POWERING UP, WHIRRING]

21:26.686 --> 21:28.321
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

21:28.355 --> 21:31.691
[MUTTERING]

21:33.025 --> 21:39.966
* You got to pick a pocket
Or two *

21:41.434 --> 21:42.969
[SIGHS]

21:44.671 --> 21:48.841
I'll show you
who's numero fucking Primo

21:48.875 --> 21:50.777
[CHAIR WHIRRING]

21:55.682 --> 21:58.885
[***]

22:02.689 --> 22:03.823
[WHIRRING]

22:05.958 --> 22:07.627
[BEEPING]

22:33.453 --> 22:35.121
[COMPUTER CHIMING]

22:56.876 --> 22:59.412
[***]

22:59.446 --> 23:03.015
ANDREWS [OVER INTERCOM]:
All right, folks, watch through
the window straight ahead.

23:03.049 --> 23:05.618
You'll be in
for a nice surprise.

23:09.656 --> 23:10.890
Is that it?

23:10.923 --> 23:12.892
Yes.

23:12.925 --> 23:17.697
Solar system 2483B65.

23:17.730 --> 23:19.799
I can tell.

23:21.768 --> 23:23.169
I can feel it in my body.

23:31.744 --> 23:34.447
ANDREWS: The old girl happy?
Yeah.

23:35.982 --> 23:38.885
ANDREWS:
We're making her dreams
come true, man.

23:38.918 --> 23:40.953
Quick spin around it,
and then we can head home.

23:42.822 --> 23:43.956
[SNIFFS]

23:46.793 --> 23:48.194
What are you gonna do
with the money?

23:48.227 --> 23:51.097
Just the question
I was asking myself.

23:52.264 --> 23:54.100
[CLICKS TONGUE]
Um...

23:54.133 --> 23:56.002
Take a tour, maybe.

23:56.035 --> 23:59.939
Figure I deserve to be
a passenger for a while.

23:59.972 --> 24:02.241
And give up the job

24:02.274 --> 24:04.544
retire some place small.

24:04.577 --> 24:05.978
Who knows?

24:06.012 --> 24:09.081
I might go live
next door to the old lady.

24:09.115 --> 24:11.484
Why? What about you?

24:11.518 --> 24:12.952
I don't know.
I do.

24:12.985 --> 24:16.789
Nice condo in Primo Central
for Barbara Norton.

24:16.823 --> 24:18.925
Ring on the finger.

24:18.958 --> 24:21.894
Dinner parties
with the smart set.

24:21.928 --> 24:24.063
It's what you want,
isn't it?

24:25.598 --> 24:27.199
Good on you, Norton.
You deserve it.

24:27.233 --> 24:29.536
I mean, me, I'm trash.

24:29.569 --> 24:31.070
I got no illusions.

24:31.103 --> 24:32.672
You?

24:32.705 --> 24:34.173
You got class.

24:34.206 --> 24:36.108
I think we should tell her.

24:38.745 --> 24:39.912
You are kidding?

24:39.946 --> 24:41.948
Emphor's just gas and rock.

24:41.981 --> 24:43.616
There isn't anything
for her to see.

24:43.650 --> 24:45.017
So?

24:46.318 --> 24:48.555
We're ripping off
an old lady

24:48.588 --> 24:51.290
so you can go on holiday,
and so I can move somewhere

24:51.323 --> 24:52.859
I don't actually wanna go.

24:52.892 --> 24:55.628
We're not
ripping anyone off.

24:55.662 --> 24:58.097
We're weaving dreams.

24:58.130 --> 25:00.600
We're artists, me and you.

25:00.633 --> 25:02.268
Con artists.

25:02.301 --> 25:04.170
What other type is there?

25:04.203 --> 25:07.607
We change mildly blue light
from meteor showers

25:07.640 --> 25:09.776
into chromatic heaven.

25:09.809 --> 25:13.179
We turn up the volume
in tiny particle collisions

25:13.212 --> 25:16.749
and make them blast
like stars exploding.

25:16.783 --> 25:18.818
Is it worth it?

25:18.851 --> 25:20.920
What are you talking about?

25:20.953 --> 25:25.124
Selling people these packages
of pre-digested happiness.

25:26.759 --> 25:28.995
I mean, there's gotta be
more than this.

25:30.329 --> 25:31.898
Hasn't there?

25:33.666 --> 25:35.568
[CONSOLE BEEPING]

25:38.638 --> 25:40.072
I'll go.

25:42.241 --> 25:43.610
[CONSOLE BEEPS]

25:43.643 --> 25:44.844
Norton.

25:46.212 --> 25:48.014
You don't say
a fucking word to her.

25:48.047 --> 25:49.582
Do you hear me?

26:00.893 --> 26:03.195
IRMA [MUFFLED]:
Hook and eyes are
very rare these days.

26:03.229 --> 26:04.664
I mean, what is the point--

26:07.299 --> 26:09.168
Oh, there you are,
Mr. Norton.

26:09.201 --> 26:10.903
I've been having
a terrible trouble

26:10.937 --> 26:12.171
with this robe.

26:12.204 --> 26:14.874
Hooks and eyes
are so rare today and...

26:14.907 --> 26:17.243
RB29 hasn't a clue
how to dress a woman.

26:17.276 --> 26:20.079
You're probably wondering
what this dress is,

26:20.112 --> 26:21.848
and where I got it from.

26:23.082 --> 26:25.117
It's my grandmother's.

26:25.151 --> 26:26.653
From Carolina.

26:26.686 --> 26:28.020
A hand-me-down to my mother

26:28.054 --> 26:30.022
and a hand-me-down
from my mother to me.

26:30.056 --> 26:32.024
I somehow kept
the moths of Riga 2

26:32.058 --> 26:33.392
from devouring it.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.695
Nothing very special.

26:35.728 --> 26:37.697
But for this occasion...

26:39.098 --> 26:40.266
Would you?

26:42.835 --> 26:45.037
[***]

26:57.116 --> 26:59.819
My grandfather would do this
for my grandmother.

27:01.220 --> 27:03.389
My mother
remembered it vividly.

27:05.057 --> 27:08.127
Of course, Bill Gordon
was quite the pioneer.

27:08.160 --> 27:09.328
He's the one that wanted

27:09.361 --> 27:11.664
to leave Earth for Riga 2.

27:11.698 --> 27:14.133
Back then,
everyone was interested in...

27:14.166 --> 27:19.071
adventure.
The unknown.

27:19.105 --> 27:22.875
Some people thought
that they might even reach God.

27:22.909 --> 27:25.878
You think you could reach God,
Mr. Norton?

27:28.380 --> 27:30.382
Maybe when I was
a kid I did.

27:33.352 --> 27:34.954
In fact, I used to dream

27:34.987 --> 27:38.090
of breaking into
whole new universes.

27:38.124 --> 27:41.360
There were still corners
we hadn't been to back then.

27:44.764 --> 27:46.966
But now it's all charted.

27:46.999 --> 27:49.168
There's no mystery anymore.

27:49.201 --> 27:51.437
Oh, but there is.

27:53.172 --> 27:55.241
People say
we know everything.

27:56.375 --> 27:59.145
Everything is explained.

27:59.178 --> 28:01.714
Down to the molecules,
the atoms,

28:01.748 --> 28:04.216
the quadrons and minimons.

28:04.250 --> 28:07.219
Every dot accounted for.

28:07.253 --> 28:09.088
But, here--

28:11.423 --> 28:15.327
Here there will always
be mystery.

28:15.361 --> 28:18.364
ANDREWS [OVER COMM]:
Folks, we are entering
the Earth's solar system.

28:18.397 --> 28:23.202
We will shortly be able
to orbit the Earth

28:23.235 --> 28:26.973
before completing
our homeward journey.

28:28.174 --> 28:29.742
What did he say?

28:29.776 --> 28:31.343
We're nearly there.

28:31.377 --> 28:34.046
[WHIRS]
Nearly where, Mr. Norton?

28:34.080 --> 28:36.082
Earth.

28:36.115 --> 28:37.316
Where else?

28:39.852 --> 28:41.888
RB29, you can go on.

28:41.921 --> 28:43.322
I have a personal question

28:43.355 --> 28:45.291
I want to ask Mr. Norton.

28:47.326 --> 28:50.029
[WHIRRING]

29:00.239 --> 29:02.809
I'm nervous.

29:02.842 --> 29:05.011
Suddenly.

29:05.044 --> 29:07.013
It's not like me.

29:10.516 --> 29:12.384
How do I look?

29:12.418 --> 29:13.786
Beautiful.

29:13.820 --> 29:15.321
[CHUCKLES]

29:15.354 --> 29:16.823
Well, thank you.

29:16.856 --> 29:18.290
You don't know what I said.

29:19.926 --> 29:21.828
Oh, but I do.

29:23.963 --> 29:26.866
I hear some people
better than others.

29:37.609 --> 29:39.111
[***]

29:39.145 --> 29:40.980
You are a gentleman,
Mr. Norton.

29:44.616 --> 29:46.418
I want
to show you something.

29:51.523 --> 29:53.092
This is my grandmother.

29:53.125 --> 29:55.194
Back in the day.

29:55.227 --> 29:57.596
And she's
with my grandfather.

29:57.629 --> 29:58.998
Bill Gordon.

30:07.573 --> 30:10.109
IRMA:
That's why when you opened
the door in the office

30:10.142 --> 30:12.879
I knew everything
would be all right.

30:12.912 --> 30:16.148
I dreamt you, Mr. Norton.

30:16.182 --> 30:18.050
Deep in my heart.

30:20.386 --> 30:23.255
And I think
maybe you dreamt me too.

30:29.128 --> 30:30.262
[***]

30:51.183 --> 30:52.952
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

30:55.421 --> 30:57.256
[SIGHS]

31:00.960 --> 31:02.228
Come on.

31:03.295 --> 31:04.430
[SIGHS]

31:06.565 --> 31:08.600
Brian, do you know
what time it is?

31:08.634 --> 31:10.569
Yeah. Uh

31:10.602 --> 31:12.538
Listen, I need to talk to you
about something.

31:12.571 --> 31:15.274
Why, is there something wrong
with the ship?

31:15.307 --> 31:17.243
No. No.

31:17.276 --> 31:19.111
Okay. Well, then
I don't really understand

31:19.145 --> 31:21.080
why this just can't wait
until tomorrow.

31:21.113 --> 31:22.614
I don't wanna live
on Primo Central.

31:24.583 --> 31:25.985
What do you mean?

31:26.018 --> 31:27.954
I mean I don't
wanna live there.

31:27.987 --> 31:30.189
I never have.

31:30.222 --> 31:31.623
I only ever wanted it
for you.

31:31.657 --> 31:33.225
Look, it's the middle
of the night,

31:33.259 --> 31:34.994
I don't wanna
talk about this now.

31:35.027 --> 31:37.429
I need to know
if you want me

31:37.463 --> 31:41.033
or if it's just that life
that you're dreaming of.

31:41.067 --> 31:44.937
I am not having
this conversation right now.

31:44.971 --> 31:47.373
Do you ever
dream about me, Barbara?

31:51.310 --> 31:53.612
You don't, do you?

31:56.348 --> 31:58.284
That's okay.

31:58.317 --> 32:00.419
I don't dream about you,
either.

32:02.388 --> 32:03.522
Not anymore.

32:05.191 --> 32:07.393
What are you trying to say?

32:07.426 --> 32:09.195
I don't know.

32:12.198 --> 32:14.066
Have you met someone else?

32:17.036 --> 32:18.337
Brian, you listen to me.

32:18.370 --> 32:20.039
I want you
to turn the ship round

32:20.072 --> 32:21.273
and get the hell back here.

32:21.307 --> 32:23.142
Right now, do you hear me?

32:23.175 --> 32:24.510
[STATIC]
Right now.

32:31.117 --> 32:32.618
What happened?
The connection went.

32:34.420 --> 32:35.721
It's fine.

32:35.754 --> 32:37.123
I've gotta go.

32:37.156 --> 32:38.324
No, talk to me.

32:38.357 --> 32:40.226
What is happening up there?

32:40.259 --> 32:42.228
It doesn't matter, Barbara.
No, Brian--

32:42.261 --> 32:43.529
Brian--

32:52.371 --> 32:53.672
[WHIRS]

32:53.705 --> 32:56.075
All right, take your time
why don't you?

32:56.108 --> 32:59.045
[OVER COMM]
We're just
passing Mars, folks.

32:59.078 --> 33:01.547
What's with the dress?
We having a hoedown?

33:01.580 --> 33:03.482
There you go, Miss Gordon.

33:03.515 --> 33:05.651
The God of War himself.

33:08.254 --> 33:11.357
No, no, no.
This is wrong.

33:11.390 --> 33:14.160
[HUFFS]
Can't you see?

33:14.193 --> 33:16.295
What are you
playing at, man?

33:16.328 --> 33:18.664
Mars is red.
Everyone knows that.

33:18.697 --> 33:20.466
I don't think so.

33:20.499 --> 33:22.334
Your memory
must be confused.

33:22.368 --> 33:24.203
I may be deaf, sir,

33:24.236 --> 33:27.106
but my mind
is as sharp as a razor.

33:27.139 --> 33:30.542
And Mars is red.

33:30.576 --> 33:32.678
[SIGHS]
Mr. Norton,
will you please tell that man

33:32.711 --> 33:34.680
to stop fooling me around.

33:34.713 --> 33:37.249
ANDREWS [OVER COMM]:
You don't say a fucking
word to her.

33:37.283 --> 33:38.684
Mr. Norton?

33:38.717 --> 33:41.120
[***]

33:41.153 --> 33:42.488
Say something.

33:42.521 --> 33:44.256
RB29:
Miss Gordon?

33:44.290 --> 33:45.457
[WHIRS]

33:45.491 --> 33:47.259
There's something
you should know.

33:49.695 --> 33:53.065
Sixty years ago there was
an electromagnetic event

33:53.099 --> 33:56.268
in Earth's solar system
causing major radioactive damage

33:56.302 --> 33:59.571
to Saturn, Mars and Venus.

33:59.605 --> 34:01.273
Saturn lost its rings.

34:01.307 --> 34:02.774
Mars turned from red

34:02.808 --> 34:04.776
to the pale green
of phosphorous.

34:04.810 --> 34:08.380
Venus became yellow
and gained one ring.

34:08.414 --> 34:09.781
Are you sure?

34:09.815 --> 34:11.483
[WHIRS]

34:15.187 --> 34:16.522
IRMA:
Mr. Norton, is this true?

34:16.555 --> 34:18.590
Yes, I'm afraid so.

34:18.624 --> 34:21.360
I'm sorry that we
didn't tell you earlier,

34:21.393 --> 34:25.397
but we...
didn't know how you'd react.

34:27.733 --> 34:30.836
[***]

34:30.869 --> 34:32.871
Oh.

34:32.904 --> 34:35.341
Venus.

34:35.374 --> 34:39.511
With one ring.
Oh, how beautiful it is. Look.

34:43.349 --> 34:46.152
One more thing, Miss Gordon.

34:46.185 --> 34:50.222
The radioactive event
changed Earth also.

34:50.256 --> 34:53.259
It's still blue

34:53.292 --> 34:55.427
but it's not
the blue of life.

35:00.766 --> 35:02.868
I understand.

35:02.901 --> 35:04.836
You're preparing me
for a shock.

35:06.638 --> 35:09.508
But as long as it's Earth

35:09.541 --> 35:11.543
I know I'll feel it.

35:11.577 --> 35:14.413
Its present state
may be different,

35:14.446 --> 35:17.816
but its history
is undeniable.

35:23.855 --> 35:25.757
Oh.

35:25.791 --> 35:27.226
Take me closer.

35:27.259 --> 35:30.128
Norton, we can't
get too close.

35:31.630 --> 35:33.365
Hold my hand.

35:41.473 --> 35:42.908
Look at it.

35:45.777 --> 35:48.247
There's an unknown here.

35:48.280 --> 35:49.881
Can't you feel it?

35:51.283 --> 35:53.252
Where's Carolina?

35:53.285 --> 35:55.554
The rest of the Earth
may be gray,

35:55.587 --> 35:58.190
but Carolina's
green and blue.

35:58.224 --> 36:00.326
And the blue
is rich and clear.

36:00.359 --> 36:04.396
Not this mud-blue of rock

36:04.430 --> 36:07.466
but the limpid blue
of a mountain stream.

36:09.335 --> 36:11.303
[SOFTLY]
I don't know
if we're gonna see that.

36:11.337 --> 36:13.339
Oh, yes we are.

36:13.372 --> 36:15.307
Close your eyes, Mr. Norton.

36:15.341 --> 36:17.309
Close your eyes with me.

36:20.379 --> 36:21.847
[***]

36:21.880 --> 36:23.315
[CONSOLE BEEPS]

36:23.349 --> 36:25.351
COMPUTER:
Color selected.

36:32.358 --> 36:33.492
[WHIRS]

36:37.429 --> 36:39.498
[SIGHS]

36:39.531 --> 36:41.700
Oh, take me down.

36:43.569 --> 36:45.504
I have to touch it.

36:45.537 --> 36:49.408
Please, let me be on Earth
for one sweet moment.

36:49.441 --> 36:51.810
No way.
We orbit the thing, then we go.

36:51.843 --> 36:54.846
[GASPS]
What-- What is he saying?

36:56.882 --> 36:58.917
Mr. Andrews said
we can land the craft.

37:05.524 --> 37:07.459
We're gonna land on Earth.

37:09.295 --> 37:11.330
We're gonna land
in Carolina.

37:13.799 --> 37:15.501
Oh, Bill.

37:20.839 --> 37:23.275
[WIND RUSHING PAST]

37:24.876 --> 37:27.513
[ROCKS PATTER]

37:31.750 --> 37:33.685
This is not safe.

37:33.719 --> 37:35.053
I can't see a fucking thing.

37:35.086 --> 37:36.822
Just keep it steady.

37:36.855 --> 37:39.024
You know, we're gonna kill her
before she lands.

37:40.692 --> 37:41.860
[CONSOLE BEEPS]

37:41.893 --> 37:43.261
Okay, set.

37:44.330 --> 37:45.631
COMPUTER:
Danger.

37:45.664 --> 37:46.832
[GRUNTS]

37:46.865 --> 37:48.967
[ENGINES REV]

37:50.669 --> 37:53.505
[COMPUTER CHIRPING]

37:53.539 --> 37:55.006
Get ready, Miss Gordon.

38:23.802 --> 38:25.437
[SILENCE]

38:25.471 --> 38:26.605
[EXPLOSION]

38:36.648 --> 38:39.017
[***]

38:39.050 --> 38:41.453
[NORTON PANTING]

38:50.929 --> 38:52.698
Irma?

38:52.731 --> 38:54.099
Irma?

38:54.132 --> 38:55.934
[GRUNTS]

38:55.967 --> 38:58.136
[DOOR BEEPS]

38:58.169 --> 39:00.005
Irma? Irma?

39:01.740 --> 39:03.975
Hey, are you okay?

39:04.009 --> 39:05.611
Irma.

39:05.644 --> 39:07.546
Hey, are you okay?

39:07.579 --> 39:09.848
Well, aren't
you the gentleman?

39:09.881 --> 39:12.451
[***]

39:24.463 --> 39:25.664
What happened to the color?

39:25.697 --> 39:27.065
Where has the color gone?

39:27.098 --> 39:28.634
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

39:28.667 --> 39:30.602
[OVER INTERCOM]
We bust the vision mixer.

39:31.737 --> 39:33.405
RB29!

39:33.439 --> 39:35.507
RB29:
We have landed
in the wrong area.

39:35.541 --> 39:37.108
We need to take off
and land again.

39:37.142 --> 39:38.877
No way.
This is as far as I go.

39:38.910 --> 39:40.746
But we need to see
Carolina.

39:40.779 --> 39:43.114
Miss Gordon wishes
to swim at Elk River.

39:43.148 --> 39:44.716
No fucking way.

39:44.750 --> 39:46.418
No one talked about swimming.

39:46.452 --> 39:48.086
This is a strictly
spectator-based

39:48.119 --> 39:49.788
tourist experience.

39:49.821 --> 39:51.590
If she wanted
the immersive element,

39:51.623 --> 39:53.592
then she should've gone
with Primo-Feel.

39:53.625 --> 39:56.528
They've got oxygen tanks,
suits, the whole thing.

39:56.562 --> 39:59.431
They walk, they swim,
they get all cuddly and cozy.

39:59.465 --> 40:00.766
We don't.

40:00.799 --> 40:02.701
Look but don't touch.

40:02.734 --> 40:06.171
This is not where
Miss Gordon wants to go.

40:06.204 --> 40:09.074
This is the only Earth
she's gonna get.

40:09.107 --> 40:11.810
And if you wanna
get back home safe,

40:11.843 --> 40:14.680
I suggest
you play ball with me.

40:14.713 --> 40:16.682
You have one hour.

40:16.715 --> 40:18.617
Then we leave.

40:23.254 --> 40:26.024
Why is Mr. Andrews so angry?

40:27.125 --> 40:28.460
He's just tired.

40:32.498 --> 40:33.632
Is this it, then?

40:36.768 --> 40:38.203
No.

40:39.838 --> 40:41.039
No, it isn't.

40:41.072 --> 40:42.207
[***]

40:48.013 --> 40:49.915
Mr. Andrews said
there weren't any suits.

40:49.948 --> 40:52.518
Mr. Andrews
doesn't know everything.

40:52.551 --> 40:54.520
Do you know
what you're doing?

40:56.788 --> 40:58.924
Yes.

40:58.957 --> 41:00.158
I do.

41:02.628 --> 41:05.196
Your Astral Dreams
viewing suit, madam.

41:05.230 --> 41:07.132
You'll have to hitch
that dress.

41:07.165 --> 41:08.934
And who's the other one for?

41:11.703 --> 41:12.838
Who do you think?

41:15.206 --> 41:18.510
Then I have one request,
Mr. Norton.

41:20.979 --> 41:23.882
[***]

41:26.752 --> 41:29.154
I have a hunch
it'll fit you perfectly.

41:32.591 --> 41:34.926
[WIND RUMBLING OUTSIDE]

41:43.569 --> 41:46.271
[THUNDER CRACKLING]

42:04.055 --> 42:05.757
How is she?

42:05.791 --> 42:07.726
RB29:
Miss Gordon is resting.

42:07.759 --> 42:10.028
She's disappointed now
but that will pass.

42:10.061 --> 42:12.564
Yeah, whatever.

42:12.598 --> 42:14.800
You know the truth, right?

42:14.833 --> 42:16.802
The truth?

42:16.835 --> 42:20.071
None of us know that,
Mr. Andrews.

42:20.105 --> 42:23.742
This planet isn't Earth for me.
But for Miss Gordon--

42:23.775 --> 42:27.178
This planet isn't fucking Earth
for anyone.

42:27.212 --> 42:30.181
It's toxic, sterile.

42:30.215 --> 42:32.784
It makes me sick
just sitting on it.

42:34.853 --> 42:37.155
I got a headache
the size of Primo Central.

42:38.757 --> 42:39.958
[SIGHS]

42:39.991 --> 42:42.060
[THUNDER CRACKLING]

42:48.834 --> 42:51.169
ANDREWS:
Oh, my eyes.

42:51.202 --> 42:53.271
[GRUNTING]

42:57.375 --> 42:59.110
[WHIRS]

42:59.144 --> 43:01.747
There's something wrong
with the temperature controls.

43:01.780 --> 43:03.882
It's baking in here.

43:03.915 --> 43:06.752
[PANTING]

43:06.785 --> 43:08.920
Norton,
where the hell are you?

43:08.954 --> 43:10.989
[THUNDER CONTINUES CRACKLING]

43:11.022 --> 43:13.391
NORTON:
Reporting status.

43:13.424 --> 43:14.760
We're moving.

43:16.294 --> 43:17.763
Visibility is low.

43:19.430 --> 43:23.101
Progress is slow but steady.

43:23.134 --> 43:25.170
Oh, Jesus, no.

43:27.739 --> 43:29.074
Norton.

43:29.107 --> 43:31.810
Those suits
only have auxiliary tanks.

43:31.843 --> 43:33.979
Miss Gordon,
this isn't Earth.

43:34.012 --> 43:35.981
Repeat,
this isn't Earth.

43:36.014 --> 43:37.182
She can't hear you.

43:40.251 --> 43:42.988
Get them back.
They're gonna die, you bastard.

43:43.021 --> 43:44.990
RB29:
You lied to her.
You stole her money.

43:46.692 --> 43:48.760
Who's the bastard?

43:50.161 --> 43:52.030
[YELLS]
Get them back right now!

44:03.474 --> 44:06.011
[BIRDS CHIRPING DISTANTLY]

44:13.819 --> 44:15.420
Do you hear that?

44:20.091 --> 44:22.227
Norton. Can you hear me?

44:22.260 --> 44:26.431
Get back here. You only have
30 percent oxygen levels.

44:26.464 --> 44:28.199
You need to get back in
right now.

44:31.770 --> 44:33.471
Repeat, can you hear me?

44:33.504 --> 44:35.874
NORTON [OVER COMMS]:
We found a forest, Ed.

44:35.907 --> 44:37.375
Okay.

44:37.408 --> 44:39.077
Just turn around, mate.

44:39.110 --> 44:41.012
Get back here.

44:42.313 --> 44:45.784
[WATER FLOWING]

44:45.817 --> 44:46.985
Listen.

44:47.018 --> 44:48.754
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

44:48.787 --> 44:50.722
I'm warning you, Norton,
I'm leaving.

44:53.825 --> 44:55.026
Can you hear it?

44:55.060 --> 44:56.227
Norton!

44:56.261 --> 44:58.029
[BEEPING RAPIDLY]

45:01.800 --> 45:03.401
I'm taking your money,
you asshole.

45:03.434 --> 45:06.972
Two kilo for me, and then
I'm fucking out of here.

45:11.476 --> 45:13.111
ANDREWS [OVER COMMS]:
Norton!

45:15.814 --> 45:17.715
[COMPUTER BEEPS RAPIDLY]

45:30.161 --> 45:32.030
[WHIRS]

45:34.499 --> 45:36.267
[YELLS]
What?

45:38.837 --> 45:41.506
[***]

45:42.941 --> 45:45.877
[BIRDS CHIRPING DISTANTLY]

46:11.402 --> 46:12.904
Irma.

46:37.095 --> 46:38.229
[WATER RUSHING]

46:40.531 --> 46:41.867
Come.

46:45.003 --> 46:49.107
[***]

47:40.959 --> 47:43.128
Bill Gordon, come on in.

48:06.952 --> 48:09.054
I knew we'd make it.

48:40.051 --> 48:41.186
[***]
